Juventus manager, Maurizio Sarri, has said Cristiano Ronaldo may not play a part in their Serie A clash against AC Milan, after developing a knee problem. Ronaldo was taken off with eight minutes left, in Wednesday’s Champions League meeting with Lokomotiv Moscow. On Sunday, the Italian champions host Milan, who sit 12th, having managed just one win from four matches. Asked for an update on Ronaldo’s fitness, Sarri told reporters: “How is Ronaldo? I still don’t know, because yesterday he was with the physiotherapists and we will see today and tomorrow in the last training session. “Let’s see what he can do. He feels a little pain in his knee but it is nothing serious.” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.